In this JSON, the specversion property indicates the version of the CloudEvents specification. The source property identifies the source of the event, which in this case is the API that generated the event. The type property indicates the type of event, in this case a credentials event. The subject property specifies the ID of the order in the event. The time property specifies the time when the event was generated. The datacontenttype property specifies the content type of the data property. The data property specifies the data that is associated with the event. The nested data object specifies the subject of the event. It contains four domain-specific fields: the order ID, the user ID of the recipient, the credential ID, and the issuance date and place.
